howItWorks: |
  <h2>How this concrete calculator works</h2>
  <p>Concrete is estimated by volume. For slabs and footings, the calculator uses length &times; width &times; thickness. For post holes, it uses the volume of a cylinder.</p>
  <h2>Why bag yield matters</h2>
  <p>Concrete bags are sold by weight, but each bag has a volume yield. For accurate bag counts, use the cubic-foot yield printed on your bag.</p>
relatedProse: |
  <p>Still deciding between concrete and pavers? Try the <a href="/calculators/paver.html">Paver Calculator</a> to compare paver material needs.</p>
  <p>Planning a wall near your concrete project? The <a href="/calculators/retaining-wall.html">Retaining Wall Calculator</a> estimates blocks, caps, and drainage gravel.</p>
  <p>Many concrete projects need a compacted base. Use the <a href="/calculators/gravel.html">Gravel Calculator</a> to estimate base gravel separately.</p>
